{
  "doc_id": "50104",
  "text": "The biological activity of A. paniculata comes from its bioactive compounds, the main class being the diterpene lactone group, which includes andrographolide, dehydroandrographolide, neoandrographolide, and deoxyandrographolide. Andrographolide occurs in higher amounts than the other diterpene lactones in A. paniculata [CITATION_1] . Flavonoids such as andrographidine, apigenin, and luteolin are also present in A. paniculata [CITATION_2] .",
